Broccoli Quiche
  --Sara, All Recipes

3 tbsp butter, divided
2 c chopped fresh broccoli
1 small onion, finely chopped
1 tsp minced garlic
9" deep-dish unbaked pie crust
1 1/2 c shredded mozzarella cheese
4 eggs, well beaten
1 1/2 c milk 
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tsp salt or to taste
1 tbsp butter, melted

Preheat the oven to 350F (175C). Melt 2 tbsp butter in a large saucepan over medium-low heat. Add broccoli, onion, and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft. Spoon vegetables into pie crust and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese; set quiche on a baking sheet. Combine eggs and milk together in a bowl; season with salt and pepper. Stir in remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter; pour egg mixture over vegetables. Bake in preheated oven until the center of the quiche has set, ~40-50 min. 


Notes: pack the cheese into the crust rather than sprinkle in. can add bell pepper or other veggies. if too wet, only use 1 c milk (or half/half0
